  description="Privacy policy for Gameye Infrastructure, including processing purposes, cookies, API data handling, and contact rights."
  canonical="https://gameye.com/privacy-policy/"
  ogType="website"
  ogImage="https://gameye.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/cropped-Gameye-server-hosting.jpg"
  ogImageAlt="Gameye Privacy Policy"
  schemaType="WebPage"
  schemaName="Privacy policy"
>
  <section class="section legal-hero">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="subtitle">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Statement of Gameye B.V.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Gameye processes personal data to operate its website, customer account workflows, and API platform
        capabilities. This page summarizes the core processing and privacy commitments.
      </p>
      <p class="updated"><strong>Last reviewed:</strong> February 18, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section legal-content">
    <div class="container narrow prose">
      <h2>1. Scope and principles</h2>
      <p>
        Gameye B.V. handles personal data in line with applicable data-protection requirements, including GDPR
        principles of purpose limitation, data minimization, security, and transparency.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Data is processed only for identified service and business purposes.</li>
        <li>Access to personal data is limited to authorized personnel and providers.</li>
        <li>Data subjects can request access, correction, deletion, or portability where applicable.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Website and account data</h2>
      <p>
        When creating or managing a customer account, Gameye may process organization and contact details such as
        company name, contact person, billing details, phone number, and email address. This processing supports
        account administration, invoicing, and service delivery.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        Gameye uses cookies and similar technologies to operate core website functionality and measure usage trends.
        Users can manage cookie preferences via browser controls and consent tooling.
      </p>
      <p>
        Third-party analytics providers may process technical usage data under their own privacy terms. Please review
        provider documentation for detailed processing behavior.
      </p>

      <h2>4. API and service data</h2>
      <p>
        Operation of multiplayer orchestration services may involve processing technical identifiers and gameplay
        telemetry required to run sessions, monitor system health, and troubleshoot incidents.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Network identifiers required for connectivity and routing.</li>
        <li>Operational telemetry related to sessions and infrastructure events.</li>
        <li>Support metadata required for diagnostics and incident response.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data sharing and transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Gameye may use vetted sub-processors to deliver hosting, observability, support, and business operations.
        Where international transfers occur, appropriate legal safeguards are applied.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Security and retention</h2>
      <p>
        Gameye applies organizational and technical safeguards intended to reduce unauthorized access, loss, or misuse
        of personal data. Retention periods depend on contractual, legal, and operational requirements.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your rights and contact</h2>
      <p>
        You can contact Gameye regarding data-processing questions or rights requests. If unresolved, you may lodge a
        complaint with your competent supervisory authority.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Gameye B.V.</strong><br />
        Goudsesingel 136<br />
        3011 KD Rotterdam<br />
        <a href="mailto:support@gameye.com">support@gameye.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingPageLayout>

